# Swift Conventions

## State Management

- Prefer the **Observation** framework (`@Observable`, `@Bindable`) over `ObservableObject`/`@StateObject`.
- Don't introduce new `ObservableObject` unless required for compatibility.
- Migrate existing `ObservableObject` usages when touching related code.

## Tooling

- **SwiftLint**: configured via `.swiftlint.yml`.
- **SwiftFormat**: configured via `.swiftformat`.
- Both are enforced in CI and pre-commit hooks.

## App Locations

| App | Path |
|-----|------|
| macOS | `apps/macos/` |
| iOS | `apps/ios/` |
| Shared | `apps/shared/` |

## Build & Test

- Mac packaging (dev): `scripts/package-mac-app.sh` (defaults to current arch).
- Release checklist: `docs/platforms/mac/release.md`.
- Do NOT rebuild the macOS app over SSH — must be run directly on the Mac.
- Before testing on device, check for connected real devices (iOS + Android) and prefer them over simulators.

## Version Locations

When bumping versions, update all of these:
- `apps/ios/Sources/Info.plist` + `apps/ios/Tests/Info.plist`
- `apps/macos/Sources/OpenClaw/Resources/Info.plist`
- `apps/android/app/build.gradle.kts`
- `package.json` (CLI)

Do NOT touch `appcast.xml` unless cutting a new macOS Sparkle release.
